{{External|rs=Fairy ring}}
[[File:Fairy ring.png|right|200px]]
The '''fairy ring''' transportation system is unlocked by [[members]] after starting the [[Fairy Tale II - Cure a Queen]] quest and getting permission from the [[Fairy Godfather]]. It consists of 45 teleportation rings spread across the world and provides a relatively fast means of accessing often remote sites in ''[[RuneScape]]'', as well as providing easy access to other realms.

Players can access the fairy ring system from any fairy ring while wielding either a [[dramen staff]] or [[lunar staff]]. From there, using three letter codes, they can teleport to most rings within the system. If the [[Lumbridge & Draynor Diary]] is fully completed, no staff of either kind is needed.

Several rings, however, require players to complete quests before they can be accessed. If the selected code has no corresponding fairy ring or is a fairy ring the player is already located in, players will not be teleported anywhere, exclaiming "''Wow, fairy magic sure is useful, I hardly moved at all!''"

Players with level 85 in [[Construction]] can build a [[Fairy ring (Construction)|fairy ring]] in their [[superior garden]].

[[File:Fairy ring teleport.gif|frame|right|The animation when using the fairy rings.]]
'''Note that [[Fairy Tale I - Growing Pains]] must be completed to access the fairy rings. [[Fairytale II - Cure a Queen]] does not need to be completed, and players do not need any of the skill requirements.'''

When using the fairy rings, a travel log will pop up. This is a list of rings to which you have recently travelled. This is useful, as you can just click on the ring code in the travel log and the code will be automatically entered. Up to four fairy ring codes can be marked as favourites for quicker code dialling to frequented rings.

==Using fairy rings==
[[File:Fairy rings selection.png|thumb|300px|The fairy ring code selection screen.]]
To use the fairy rings, players must complete the following quests:
*[[The Restless Ghost]]
*[[Priest in Peril]]
*[[Nature Spirit]]
*[[Lost City]]
*[[Fairytale I - Growing Pains]]
*Started [[Fairytale II - Cure a Queen]]

One may quickly access the fairy rings in any of the following ways:
*[[Player-owned house]] fairy ring ({{Fairycode|diq}}) placed inside [[Superior Garden]]. '''(~5 tiles)'''
*[[Quest point cape]] teleport to [[Legends' Guild]], near fairy ring {{Fairycode|blr}}. '''(12 tiles)''' 
*[[Slayer ring]] teleport to the [[Fremennik Slayer Dungeon]] east of fairy ring {{Fairycode|ajr}}. '''(16 tiles)'''
*[[Achievement diary cape]] teleport to Le-sabr√® east of fairy ring {{Fairycode|cks}} '''(20 tiles)'''
*[[Salve Graveyard Teleport]] (or its [[Salve graveyard teleport|magic tablet variant]]) west of fairy ring {{Fairycode|cks}}. '''(22 tiles)'''
*[[Arceuus Library Teleport]] takes players south of fairy ring {{Fairycode|cis}} '''(34 tiles)'''
*[[Necklace of passage]] teleport to the [[Wizards' Tower]] north of fairy ring {{Fairycode|dis}}. '''(39 tiles)'''
*[[Ring of wealth]] teleport to [[Miscellania]] south-east of fairy ring {{Fairycode|CIP}}. '''(48 tiles)'''
*[[Yanille teleport]] or [[Teleport to House]] if the player's [[player-owned house|house]] is in [[Yanille]] - go through the western gates of Yanille then travel north to fairy ring {{Fairycode|ciq}}. '''(60 tiles)'''
*[[Ardougne cloak]] teleport to [[Ardougne Monastery]] and travel east slightly past the [[Tower of Life (building)|Tower of Life]] to fairy ring {{Fairycode|djp}}. '''(80 tiles)'''
*[[Ring of wealth]], or [[Varrock Teleport]] with completion of the [[Varrock Diary#Medium|medium Varrock diary]], to teleport to the [[Grand Exchange]] - travel north-west until you reach the level 21 [[Agility shortcut]], running south until you reach fairy ring {{Fairycode|DKR}}. '''(82 tiles)'''
**Those without level 21 [[Agility]] may travel west outside of the [[Grand Exchange]] wall and head north through a fence to get to fairy ring {{Fairycode|DKR}}.
*[[Amulet of glory]] teleport to [[Edgeville]] - travel east across the small bridge and head south to reach fairy ring {{Fairycode|DKR}}. '''(90 tiles)'''
*Use an [[Ectophial]] then run south-west to fairy ring {{Fairycode|alq}}. '''(92 tiles)'''
*[[Farming Guild]] teleport using either a [[skills necklace]] or [[farming cape]] - leave the guild and run north-east to get to fairy ring {{Fairycode|CIR}}. '''(106 tiles)'''

Closest points of interest to fairy rings:
*Bank - Chasm of Fire {{Fairycode|djr}} (29 tiles) to a Shayzien bank chest.
**Players that have have both a [[Spirit tree (Construction)|Spirit Tree]] and fairy ring in their POH may use the [[Farming Guild]] for quicker bank access. This requires 85 [[farming]] and a Spirit Tree in the Farming Guild.
*Altar - Mudskipper Point {{Fairycode|aiq}} (84 tiles) (or POH chapel/pool via {{Fairycode|diq}} if this has been built in the [[Superior Garden]]).
**Alternatively, one can use {{Fairycode|bip}} to reach the Nature grotto altar with 50 agility (54 tiles and a shortcut). This altar also boosts your prayer by two points over your level. 

''Note: Tiles are measured without diagonal steps and may be more or less based on teleport deviation.''

